The repeated patterns in browser-commands.ts:

1. Tab ID validation (appears ~25 times):
```ts
const tabId = params.tabId;
if (typeof tabId !== 'number') {
  sendToServer({ jsonrpc: '2.0', error: { code: -32602, message: 'Missing or invalid tabId parameter' }, id });
  return;
}
```

2. Selector validation (appears ~8 times):
```ts
const selector = params.selector;
if (typeof selector !== 'string' || selector.length === 0) {
  sendToServer({ jsonrpc: '2.0', error: { code: -32602, message: 'Missing or invalid selector parameter' }, id });
  return;
}
```

3. URL validation with blocked scheme check (appears ~5 times):
```ts
if (typeof url !== 'string') { ... }
if (isBlockedUrlScheme(url)) { ... }
```

4. Script result extraction (appears ~15 times):
```ts
const result = results[0]?.result as SomeType | undefined;
if (!result) {
  sendToServer({ jsonrpc: '2.0', error: { code: -32603, message: 'No result from script execution' }, id });
  return;
}
if (result.error) {
  sendToServer({ jsonrpc: '2.0', error: { code: -32602, message: result.error }, id });
  return;
}
```

5. Error catch block (appears ~30 times):
```ts
catch (err) {
  sendToServer({ jsonrpc: '2.0', error: { code: -32603, message: sanitizeErrorMessage(toErrorMessage(err)) }, id });
}
```

Only convert 5+ handlers as a demonstration — converting all 30+ handlers in one story is too large. Pick handlers from different submodules to prove the pattern works across modules.

Import the helpers in the submodule files. The helpers file imports sendToServer from '../messaging.js', sanitizeErrorMessage from '../sanitize-error.js', toErrorMessage and isBlockedUrlScheme from '@opentabs-dev/shared'.
